title: LOVE Sri Lanka
description:
Sri Lanka , formerly known as Ceylon and officially the Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka, is an island country in South Asia. It lies in the Indian Ocean, southwest of the Bay of Bengal, and southeast of the Arabian Sea; it is separated from the Indian subcontinent by the Gulf of Mannar and the Palk Strait. Sri Lanka shares a maritime border with India and the Maldives. Sri Jayawardenepura Kotte is its legislative capital, and Colombo is its largest city and financial centre.

Sri Lanka has a population of around 22 million (2020) and is a multinational state, home to diverse cultures, languages, and ethnicities. The Sinhalese are the majority of the nation's population. Other long established groups include the Tamils, the Moors, the Burghers, the Malays, the Chinese, and the indigenous Vedda.

Sri Lanka's documented history goes back 3,000 years, with evidence of prehistoric human settlements that dates back at least 125,000 years.

Sri Lanka is a developing country

title: ANAT- AV
description:
With the vast breadth of the subject of anatomy, ranging from simple basics to minute yet important detail, the need for detailed, accurate, yet concise methods of learning and revising anatomy need not be stressed. We at ANAT- AV strive to provide videos of highly accurate, easy to understand information in as short a time as possible- no more watching hour-long videos for a single organ! In addition, we focus on making our videos primarily from cadaveric dissections, as they provide one of the most realistic methods of teaching and learning anatomy.

We hope you will benefit from this channel as both students and practitioners!
Thank you for watching ANAT- AV.

ANAT- AV was created and is run by the medical students of the Anatomical Society of the Faculty of Medicine, University of Colombo, Sri Lanka.
To assure the quality of the information provided, all videos pass through the esteemed panel of lecturers at the Department of Anatomy of said medical faculty.

Please note that our channel is for educational purposes only and is managed by an Admin. For medical concerns, seek prompt attention from a qualified healthcare provider.

Prof. Probhodana Ranaweera.
MBBS (CoLMD) (Obs & Gynae); MRCOG (UK); Diploma in Laparoscopic Surgery (France); Hon. Consultant Obstetrician and Gynaecologist

Prof. Probhodana is a quintessential medical professional, researcher and an educator who is working with a vision towards ensuring respectful medical care to women throughout their life. He graduated from the Faculty of Medicine, University of Colombo in 2005. He works as an honorary Consultant Obstetrician and Gynaecologist attached to the De Soysa Maternity Hospital for Women and National Hospital of Sri Lanka.  He is also a Professor at the Department of Obstetrics & Gynaecology, Faculty of Medicine, University of Colombo.
